        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-12-12T23:47:48.643Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Related alternative solution:</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"26690\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/35a633/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/load-the-link-preview-after-sending-message/26690\">Load the link preview after sending message</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    It can be quite annoying when trying to send a video-site link, article etc. to a friend, and wait for the thumbnail to load properly, because if it‚Äôs not, it will be sent without one. \nPlease add an option to settings (or even turn it on by default) that automatically includes a thumbnail, even after you press enter to send a message, so we can just send it and expect the thumbnail to load anyways, basically like other messaging apps. \nThe app can just automatically send a message when the thum‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
